<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2148: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-21T03:00:00+08:00">October
                                    21, 1948—3 a. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:32 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>293. KMA at Tangshan reports arrival there of units of Taiwan trained
                            army which recently arrived at Tangku. Mines area quiet.</p>
                        <p>Chinese press reported Changli again occupied by Communists. Apparently
                            no Govt troops there.</p>
                        <p>Sent Nanking 536, repeated Department 293, Peiping.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>